chapters.teach:
Un programme Rust :

```rust
fn main() {
    println!("Bonjour");
}
```

`println!` est une **macro** (le `!` le signale).

```rust
let nom = "ANIMA";
println!("{}", nom);
```

`{}` est remplacé par la valeur.

chapters.correction:
fn main() {
    let nom = "ANIMA";
    println!("{}", nom);
}

fn main() {
    let total = 20 + 22;
    println!("Total : {}", total);
}

fn main() {
    let x = 7;
    if x > 5 {
        println!("VERROUILLE");
    }
}

fn main() {
    for i in 1..=5 {
        println!("{}", i);
    }
}

fn main() {
    let a = vec![10, 20, 30];
    println!("{}", a[0]);
}

